This paper is about entity linking, which is a natural language processing task. The paper specifically focuses on entity disambiguation in noisy text, which suggests that it may fall under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper mentions applications such as semantic search and knowledge graph construction, which are related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of a semantic similarity engine also suggests that this paper may fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper mentions the use of a local embedded database, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of databases (cs.DB).
